Rules:
Special Rule: "Upward Mobility" 
When a unit is touching the base of one of the small staircases leading to the top of the fortress wall, consider the vertical distance to the top of the wall as 3" instead of 6" for the purposes of movement. The idea is that the staircases give an advantage to the defender by allowing his units to ascend the wall rapidly.
